description.plain:
Frankie Jahmier Childress (b. on July 6th, 1998), better known by his stage name Comethazine, is a rapper repping East St. Louis. Comethazine said in an interview with Mass Appeal that his name comes from the mix of both his nickname in high school, Cocaine, and the drug Promethazine. He got his “Cocaine” nickname for his light skin as opposed to his friends'.

Comethazine started rapping in his basement a few years prior to his EP, Aloe Vera, dropping on iTunes in August of 2016. After dropping the EP, he gained traction with the songs, “Run It” and “Hella Choppers”.

Comethazine has stated in interviews that his influences include 50 Cent, Chief Keef, and Rick James. He is currently signed to Todd Moscowitz’s Alamo Records.

songs.title: Walk

description.plain:
“Walk” is the first track on Comethazine’s first album in the “Bawskee” series, named “Bawskee” or also known as “Bawskee 1”

On it, the St. Louis rapper briefly mentions his lavish lifestyle, and about how he is ready to shoot his opponent with his chopper, if necessary.

To date, “Walk” is Comethazine’s most popular song and was released on August 24, 2018.

The song uses the sample from Looperman “Flutething idk”. In the song, the sample is reversed and pitched up.

songs.title: Bands

description.plain:
“BANDS” hit number one on the SoundCloud charts for a short period of time due to an account called SoundClout, switching the track in place of YBN Nahmir’s “Bounce Out With That.”

It is produced by Portuguese producer, Foreign Heat. The original instrumental can be found on his SoundCloud.

songs.title: SOLVED THE PROBLEM

description.plain:
On “SOLVED THE PROBLEM”, East St. Louis, Illinois rapper Comethazine raps about his gang lifestyle and selling drugs. The track is widely seen as the most anticipated release from Comethazine’s upcoming album, BAWSKEE 3.5.

This tracks was originally previewed on Comethazine’s Instagram on February 17th, 2019 via a Triller video.
